{
  "texts": [
    "GB1 refers to the B1 domain of protein G, an immunoglobin binding protein where fitness is measured by binding affinity-based sequence enrichment.",
    "The fitness of TrpB, the β-subunit of tryptophan synthase, was measured by coupling growth to the rate of tryptophan formation.",
    "Our baseline was DE greedy walk, where one residue was mutated to all possible amino acids, the best mutation was fixed, and the process was repeated at each of the residues under study (Fig. 4A).",
    "DE simulations were performed from all active variants as starting points, using all 24 possible orders to enumerate the residues under interest.",
    "The ALDE simulation consisted of batch BO, as shown in Fig. 4B."
  ]
}